  "texts": [
    "Applications that include generative AI can contribute to the provision of learning feedback, assist in translation, help create learning activities, and construct natural dialogue scenarios for language learning [9][10][11].",
    "However, a recent empirical case study by Kohnke et al. [12] points to the need for specific and targeted education in using generative AI for instructors (and their students), such as prompt engineering and redesigning learning for the new AI environments.Part of the attraction of this new technology is the facility of generative AI to adapt learning content and provide targeted digital feedback that can support the work of teachers in language education [13].",
    "Traditional approaches to language learning, while effective in some instances, often adopt a one-size-fits-all approach that is being reconsidered for digital times where the scope of learning resources available to students is much greater [14].",
    "Potentially, AI-based tools can evaluate individual learning patterns, adjust the curriculum accordingly, and provide instant feedback in online and flipped learning environments [15].",
    "This can augment the work of teachers in the learning process and cater to individual learning styles and needs."
  ],
